### WebFlux Docker Demo - API Requests
### Use with VS Code REST Client or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Simple Hello Endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/hello

### 2. Application Information
GET {{baseUrl}}/info
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 3. Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 4. Async Operation with 5 Second Delay
GET {{baseUrl}}/async-delay/5

### 5. Reactive Chain with Processing
GET {{baseUrl}}/reactive-chain/10
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 6. Reactive Chain with Invalid Input (should error)
GET {{baseUrl}}/reactive-chain/-5
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 7. Server-Sent Events Stream
GET {{baseUrl}}/stream
Accept: text/event-stream

### 8. Numbers Stream (100 values)
GET {{baseUrl}}/numbers
Accept: text/event-stream

### 9. Spring Boot Health Endpoint
GET http://localhost:8080/health

### 10. Application Metrics
GET http://localhost:8080/metrics

---

### Notes:
# - For stream endpoints, the client should support chunked transfer encoding
# - SSE streams continuously until they reach their completion
# - The /api/stream endpoint sends 10 events at 1-second intervals
# - The /api/numbers endpoint sends 100 numbers with 100ms delays between each
# - The /api/reactive-chain endpoint processes input with a 500ms delay
#
# To test with curl:
# curl http://localhost:8080/api/hello
# curl http://localhost:8080/api/stream
# curl http://localhost:8080/api/async-delay/3
#
# To test with PowerShell:
# .\test-api.ps1
#
# To test with Bash:
# bash test-api.sh

